description:
Real organic fruit. 3 generations. Non GMO Project: Verified. Fairtrade. USDA organic. We're so happy our paths have crossed. Was it the trail of sweet strawberries and just a touch of honey that led you here? Maybe you were looking for a tasty treat when you came upon real organic fruit in a deliciously toasted pastry. Or, did you just want a quick snack? Whatever your reason for winding up on Nature's Path, we're glad you did. Let us know how your journey's going and how we can make it better. We'll see you on the path - how about snack time, some time tomorrow? Non-GMO. Real organic fruit. Certified organic. Growing up on an organic farm, I learned a lot about caring for the land and the importance of good stewardship. As my father Rupert used to say, always leave the Earth better than you found it. Those wise words flavor everything we do here at Nature's Path. - Arran Stephens, Founder & Garden-keeper. Deliciously organic & naturally flavored, they have real fruit & whole grain content. Enjoy them straight from the package or warmed in the toaster! Quality Assurance International certified organic. 100% recycled paperboard. Cane sugar, invert cane syrup, molasses, honey, and vanilla traded in compliance with Fairtrade standards, total 36%. Our 100% certified sustainable palm oil is always ethically sourced. Vegetarian. This product is third-party certified organic by Quality Assurance International (QAI). Quality Guarantee: Not feeling the love? If you're less than thrilled with this product, let us know. Product of USA.

Directions
Toaster Style (Optimal Method): Remove wrapper and place your Nature's Path Organic Toaster Pastry in toaster on light or lowest heat setting. Allow toaster pastry to cool before handling (Caution: Frosting and filling can become very hot and cause burns after being heated). Microwave Style: Remove Toaster Pastry from its foil pouch and microwave on high for 10 seconds. Allow Toaster Pastry to cool before handling (Caution: Frosting and filling can become very hot and cause burns after being heated). Be sure to allow for adequate cooling time before handling and eating. Use lowest settings on toasters and never leave your toaster or microwave unattended while heating due to the chance of smoke and fire. Children should be supervised while heating pastries.
